This folder 'Phenology' contains code that analyses Dinophysis phenology sensu lato.

The files 'GAM ...' are R scripts used for fitting Generalized Additive Models to phytoplankton count data, for Mesodinium and Dinophysis (and 2 other dinos).

The file 'Dino phenology analysis REPHY.R' is a R script for analysing Dinophysis phenology without models (violin plots mainly)

The file 'Numerical ecophysiology' explores the dynamics of parameters from GAM models in relation to environmental or biotic variables
